commitResults.messageTitle: Working skeletal functions for the chatbot

Added 3 new classes TodoTask, DeadlineTask and EventTask
Editted the input splitter function to accomodate todo, event, deadine
Implemented the deadine, todo and event tasks into Duke
Now Duke will track the amount of tasks you have as you add in new tasks.
Implemented the UI testing component and modified some of the inputSplit function such that errorenous inputs will not be passed into the tasks.
Added the DukeException Exception and modified Duke to make use of it.
Previous commit accidentally commited an incomplete implementation of DukeException. This one is complete.
Add a Map containing constructors for tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Addition of Map consolidates constructors for various tasks into a
single data structure, reducing repeated codes within Duke.

Initially, Duke has many repeated codes for the various cases depending
on what is the task called.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Map taskOperations
commitResults.messageBody:
This map contains the functions that specify how to deal with the
various user commands within Duke.

The code is initially lengthened by the use of if else statements to
check for various commands. Now they are replaced with a single
encompassing if statement that retrieves the required function to handle
user request.

commitResults.messageBody:
Now Duke is able to retrieve data from a text file saved within the data

commitResults.messageTitle: Add function to write tasks to disk
commitResults.messageBody:
Now Duke is able to write the tasklist to disk, allowing future
rebooting of Duke to access the same tasklist
